Description:
We are looking for a WordPress developer who has strong skills in PHP, Laravel, and LearnDash LMS. You will be responsible for creating and maintaining WordPress websites, plugins, and themes using the latest web technologies and best practices. You will also work with LearnDash LMS to create engaging and interactive online courses and learning experiences. 
## Responsibilities 
- Develop and maintain WordPress websites, plugins, and themes using PHP, Laravel, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and other web technologies. 
- Customize and extend LearnDash LMS functionality using hooks, filters, actions, and custom code. 
- Create and manage online courses, quizzes, certificates, badges, reports, and other learning features using LearnDash LMS. 
- Ensure high-quality code standards, performance, security, and compatibility across different browsers and devices. 
- Troubleshoot and debug issues and provide technical support to clients and users. 
- Collaborate with other developers, designers, project managers, and stakeholders to deliver successful projects. 
## Requirements 
- Proven experience as a WordPress developer with a portfolio of WordPress projects. 
- Strong knowledge of PHP, Laravel, and object-oriented programming principles. 
- Experience with LearnDash LMS or other WordPress-based learning management systems. 
- Familiarity with WordPress coding standards, APIs, hooks, filters, actions, and custom post types. 
- Proficiency in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, jQuery, Bootstrap, and other front-end technologies. 
- Experience with Git or other version control systems. 
- Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment. 
- Excellent communication and problem-solving skills. 
- Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field or equivalent work experience.
